ordination. Intended for general readers as well as scholars, Shameless extends the boundaries of classics and anthropology, forming a model of the sensitive work that can be done to illuminate how deeply animals are imbricated in human history. The English translation has been revised and expanded from the original Italian edition, and it includes a new methodological appendix by the author that points the way toward future work in the emerging field of human-animal studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDogs in literature. 0aDogsxMythologyzGreece. 0aGreek literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aWomen in literature. 0aWomenxMythologyzGreece. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aancient greece.  aanimals.  aanthropology.  acanine.  aclassical literature.  acomic jokes.  acomplex relationships.  aconceptual tools.  acritical analysis.  acultural meaning.  aculture.  adogs.  aenglish translation.  afeminine subordination.  afigure of the dog.  agender and womens studies.  agender studies.  agender.  agreek imagination.  ahuman animal studies.  ahuman history.  ahumans and dogs.  ametaphors.  amethodology.  amyth.  amythology.  amyths.  anegative connotations.  apast cultures.  apresent cultures.  aproverbs.  aself control.  aspiritual.  awomen and dogs.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052027340540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095742840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957428423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957428/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY